>  [four key types](https://www.advisory.com/daily-briefing/2014/08/08/optimism-v-pessimism-which-is-healthier) of optimism and pessimism By Dilip Jeste
>  1.  **Dispositional** **optimism and pessimism**.  
    How our personality (nature & nurture) guides our future expectations (positive or negative).
    2.  **Strategic optimism**.  
    Thinking and feeling that focuses on upsides and opportunities when faced with potential risks and stresses.
    3.  **Defensive pessimism**.  
    Thinking and feeling that lowers expectations and anticipates bad outcomes when faced with risks and stresses.
    4.  **Explanatory** **optimism and pessimism**.  
    The ways we explain the causes of good and bad outcomes, and explain our ability to influence them.
